item.title: Item ID's
item.dc:creator: @Taios Taios
item.description:
@Taios wrote:

zyle1992:

sorta. im trying to figure out how to get the info off the deob. like what the id’s of the skill capes are, what the id of a gilded 4-poster bed is, and stuf like that.[br][size=1]Posted on: July 20, 2007, 06:52:07 PM[/size][hr]can someone help me with this?

theres a method in the deob that takes in all actions. Action ID’s, npc, object, menu action names, interface uids, index ids.
Find that and print out in there :). It will print out the id’s each time you move over and item, npc or w/e.
Anotherway to do it is to find the item array id array’s, and names. Loop through them both and print them out to a file. Then do the same for npc’s and objects if thats what you wish to do.
If you need any further help, finding the methods etc. Have a go and then reply :).
